title: EveningLedger_M1_Day1_Standard
tags: ledger mission1 day1 prose
---
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Mission 1 — Evening Ledger Day 1 prose.
// Author: Esme Cordray (Choice & Consequence Architect)
// Spec:   Docs/Depth_Bible/Mission_1_2_Focus/07_DIALOGUE_AND_LEDGER_UI.md § 4
// Guide:  Docs/GAMEPLAY_GUIDE_MISSION_1.md § 16
//
// The cozy game's first save = the act of closing this book at the end of
// the day. Two variants for M1:
//   • Standard — Doris's orb on the shelf, after Polish.
//   • Refusal  — Doris's orb declined, no Polish, no dream.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

LedgerPage_Left: Day 1 — Spire-Month, Week 1
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: You arrived at the Hollow this evening.
LedgerPage_Left: The door was unlocked. The kettle was warm.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: Doris, the baker, was your first visitor.
LedgerPage_Left: She offered her First Loaves — a memory from the morning her bakery opened, fifty years ago.
LedgerPage_Left: You polished it. You did your work. She seemed pleased.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: Pickle, the cat who lives in the shop, was on the windowsill.
LedgerPage_Left: She did not move. She is watching you.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: The shop is quiet. The shelf is no longer empty.

LedgerPage_Right:
LedgerPage_Right: Open work:
LedgerPage_Right:
LedgerPage_Right: — Doris's First Loaves is on the shelf. You may return to it any morning.
LedgerPage_Right: — The shop has three more empty shelves. The Keeper before you left them.
LedgerPage_Right: — There is a locked room upstairs. The door is heavy.
LedgerPage_Right: — There is a man at the lane's bend, walking with a letter. You did not speak to him.
LedgerPage_Right:
LedgerPage_Right: Hollow Level 1 — the shop is open for business.

===

title: EveningLedger_M1_Day1_Refused
tags: ledger mission1 day1 prose refusal
---
// Variant — player refused Doris's orb in Mission 1 (Doris_M1_RefusedPath).
// Mission 1 Guide § 9.4: "The cozy contract holds."

LedgerPage_Left: Day 1 — Spire-Month, Week 1
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: You arrived at the Hollow.
LedgerPage_Left: The door was unlocked. The kettle was warm.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: Doris, the baker, offered her First Loaves.
LedgerPage_Left: You declined, this evening.
LedgerPage_Left: She did not seem to mind.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: The shop is still yours.
LedgerPage_Left: Some days are not the day.

LedgerPage_Right:
LedgerPage_Right: Open work:
LedgerPage_Right:
LedgerPage_Right: — Doris may return another day. She did not seem in a hurry.
LedgerPage_Right: — The shop has four empty shelves. The Keeper before you left them so.
LedgerPage_Right: — There is a locked room upstairs. The door is heavy.
LedgerPage_Right: — There is a man at the lane's bend, walking with a letter. You did not speak to him.
LedgerPage_Right:
LedgerPage_Right: Hollow Level 1 — the shop is open for business.

===

title: EveningLedger_VowGlyphs_Day1
tags: ledger mission1 vows
---
// Bottom-of-left-page Vow glyph state for Day 1. Brighter glyphs = higher
// integrity. The cozy game's only HUD visualization of moral state.
// Per Mission 1 Guide § 16.1.

VowGlyph: ⊙ Consent — kept
VowGlyph: ⊙ Return — untested
VowGlyph: ⊙ Whole — kept
VowGlyph: ⊙ Quiet Glass — untested
VowGlyph: ⊙ Honest Coin — kept
VowGlyph: ⊙ Open Door — untested
VowGlyph: ⊙ Last Light — untested

===

title: VowReflection_Vow1_Consent
tags: ledger vow reflection marin
---
// Player clicks a Vow glyph in the Ledger → Marin's hand-written reflection.
// Per Mission 1 Guide § 16.2 + Mission 2 Guide § 21.

MarinReflection: Consent — the first vow. The hardest to remember during a long day. — M.

===

title: VowReflection_Vow2_Return
tags: ledger vow reflection marin
---
MarinReflection: Return — the easiest vow to write down. The hardest to live. — M.

===

title: VowReflection_Vow3_Whole
tags: ledger vow reflection marin
---
MarinReflection: Whole — a memory should leave your shop as the bearer asked for. Never less. — M.

===

title: VowReflection_Vow4_QuietGlass
tags: ledger vow reflection marin
---
MarinReflection: Quiet Glass — an orb on a shelf is not a story to tell. It is a person, kept. — M.

===

title: VowReflection_Vow5_HonestCoin
tags: ledger vow reflection marin
---
MarinReflection: Honest Coin — charge what the memory is worth. Refuse what it is not. Even your own kindness can be a kind of dishonesty. — M.

===

title: VowReflection_Vow6_OpenDoor
tags: ledger vow reflection marin
---
MarinReflection: Open Door — the Hollow is open to anyone. Even the ones who broke the last vow. — M.

===

title: VowReflection_Vow7_LastLight
tags: ledger vow reflection marin
---
MarinReflection: Last Light — sometimes the best work a Keeper can do is sit beside the bearer. Some memories should not be transacted at all. — M.

===

title: EveningLedger_M2_Day2_VariantA_CleansePerfect
tags: ledger mission2 day2 prose variant_a
---
// Mission 2 Day 2 — Variant A: Cleanse Perfect outcome (best Cleanse path).
// Per Mission 2 Guide § 21.1.1.

LedgerPage_Left: Day 2 — Spire-Month, Week 1
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: Gerrold Pell, the widower, came to the Hollow at half past seven.
LedgerPage_Left: He brought a memory wrapped in his wife's handkerchief.
LedgerPage_Left: You took it. You did the work. The work was clean.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: You walked to his cottage. You sat in his chair.
LedgerPage_Left: You returned the handkerchief.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: Margery Pell, who died last winter, is now a clearer memory than she was this morning.
LedgerPage_Left: The man who carried her will sleep tonight.

===

title: EveningLedger_M2_Day2_VariantB_CleanseAcceptable
tags: ledger mission2 day2 prose variant_b
---
// Variant B — Cleanse Acceptable or Sloppy.

LedgerPage_Left: Day 2 — Spire-Month, Week 1
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: Gerrold Pell, the widower, came to the Hollow at half past seven.
LedgerPage_Left: He brought a memory wrapped in his wife's handkerchief.
LedgerPage_Left: You took it. You worked carefully.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: You walked to his cottage. The fire was warm.
LedgerPage_Left: You returned the handkerchief.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: Margery Pell is gentler in his memory than she was this morning.
LedgerPage_Left: The long bit is no longer the whole of it.

===

title: EveningLedger_M2_Day2_VariantC_Damaged
tags: ledger mission2 day2 prose variant_c
---
// Variant C — Erase path (any outcome) OR Cleanse Crossed-Core.

LedgerPage_Left: Day 2 — Spire-Month, Week 1
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: Gerrold Pell brought a memory.
LedgerPage_Left: You took it. The work did not go as planned.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: He thanked you. He is going home.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: His wife's face, in his memory, is no longer entirely her own.

===

title: EveningLedger_M2_Day2_VariantD_Listen
tags: ledger mission2 day2 prose variant_d listen warmest
---
// Variant D — Listen path. The warmest possible Day 2 Ledger prose.
// Per Mission 2 Guide § 21.1.4.

LedgerPage_Left: Day 2 — Spire-Month, Week 1
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: Gerrold Pell brought a memory.
LedgerPage_Left: You declined to take it.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: You sat in his cottage for three hours while he spoke.
LedgerPage_Left: He told you everything.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: He still has the memory.
LedgerPage_Left: He is no longer alone with it.

===

title: EveningLedger_M2_Day2_VariantE_Defer
tags: ledger mission2 day2 prose variant_e defer
---
// Variant E — Defer path. Mission 2 ends with the choice still open.

LedgerPage_Left: Day 2 — Spire-Month, Week 1
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: Gerrold Pell brought a memory.
LedgerPage_Left: You asked him to come back tomorrow.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: He thanked you for the consideration.
LedgerPage_Left: He took the cloth home.
LedgerPage_Left:
LedgerPage_Left: The orb is in his cottage tonight.
LedgerPage_Left: The choice is still open.

===
